# UI Component Implementation Rules

## UI Framework
- Next.js 15+ with App Router
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Server/Client Components

## Component Structure (rel to `/website/src/`)
- `components/` - Shared components
- `app/[feature]/components/` - Feature-specific
- App Router for page organization
- Layouts for shared UI elements

## Best Practices
- Default to Server Components
- "use client" only when needed (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- Single responsibility per component
- Composition over inheritance
- Extract reusable UI elements

## Styling Guidelines
- Tailwind CSS classes
- Mobile-first responsive design
- CSS variables for theming
- Consistent spacing via Tailwind
- Semantic HTML + ARIA

## Form Handling
- React Hook Form for complex forms
- Proper validation with errors
- Handle loading/error/success states
- Accessible forms (labels, errors, focus)

## Data Fetching
- Server Components for initial fetch
- SWR/React Query for client-side
- UI feedback for loading/errors
- Optimistic UI when appropriate

## Multi-Tenant UI
- Respect org context in UI
- Permission-based content display
- Clear org context indicators

## Admin Interfaces
- Consistent admin patterns
- Data tables with actions
- Filtering, sorting, pagination
- Clear action feedback
- Confirm destructive actions

## Accessibility
- Sufficient color contrast
- Alt text for images
- Keyboard accessibility
- Semantic HTML + ARIA
- Screen reader testing 